WEBVTT

00:10.267 --> 00:11.332
<i> PREVIOUSLY ON "GREENLEAF"...</i>

00:11.334 --> 00:13.132
IN THE EVENT THAT THINGS
BETWEEN YOUR PARENTS

00:13.134 --> 00:14.865
TAKE YET ANOTHER TURN
FOR THE WORSE,

00:14.867 --> 00:16.531
THE DEACONS MAY ASK YOU
TO STEP UP.

00:16.533 --> 00:18.898
-STEP UP?
-TAKE OVER AS HEAD PASTOR.

00:18.900 --> 00:22.465
I'M DIVORCING JAMES.
I WANT TO START MY OWN CHURCH.

00:22.467 --> 00:24.932
GIRL, YOU ALREADY GOT
A PERFECTLY GOOD ONE.

00:24.934 --> 00:27.465
-WHICH ONE?
-CALVARY, HONEY.

00:27.467 --> 00:28.999
I COULD REALLY
SLAP YOU RIGHT NOW.

00:29.001 --> 00:32.332
GO AHEAD. DO IT!

00:32.334 --> 00:33.332
GIRLS!

00:33.334 --> 00:34.732
HOW MUCH MORE
SPACE DO YOU NEED?

00:34.734 --> 00:35.799
YOU SHOULDN'T
BE HERE.

00:35.801 --> 00:37.198
IF I WAS
YOUR MONEY MANAGER,

00:37.200 --> 00:40.231
I WOULD DEFINITELY ADVISE YOU
TO MAKE SURE YOU'RE PROTECTED.

00:40.233 --> 00:42.332
I'M THINKING IT MIGHT
BE WISE FOR US

00:42.334 --> 00:45.632
TO SIT DOWN
WITH MY MONEY PEOPLE.

00:45.634 --> 00:47.299
STOP. DON'T BE MAD.

00:47.301 --> 00:50.532
LOOK, I'M NOT.
I'LL CALL YOU LATER.

00:50.534 --> 00:51.798
Officer: MA'AM, ARE YOU
CHARITY GREENLEAF?

00:51.800 --> 00:52.999
I NEED YOU
TO COME WITH US.

00:55.867 --> 00:57.699
ZORA'S ROOM.

01:03.034 --> 01:05.065
Mae: OH, LORD.

01:07.600 --> 01:08.998
BABIES.

01:09.000 --> 01:10.132
[ INTERCOM BUZZING ]

01:10.134 --> 01:14.398
-FIRST LADY?
-YES?

01:14.400 --> 01:18.132
-NANA CLARA IS ON LINE ONE.
-WONDERFUL, WONDERFUL.

01:18.134 --> 01:19.565
THANK YOU, JESUS.

01:21.867 --> 01:24.798
CLARA, HELLO.

01:24.800 --> 01:28.265
OH, YES.
WE'VE BEEN EXPECTING YOUR CALL.

01:28.267 --> 01:30.398
I CANNOT TELL YOU
HOW MUCH BISHOP

01:30.400 --> 01:32.899
AND I APPRECIATE
YOUR GENEROSITY.

01:34.867 --> 01:36.399
WHA --?

01:41.067 --> 01:43.598
CLARA IS NOT
GIVING US THE MONEY.

01:43.600 --> 01:45.798
I KNOW. I JUST GOT OFF THE
PHONE WITH HER MONEY MANAGER.

01:45.800 --> 01:47.399
WHAT A PIECE OF WORK
THAT MAN IS.

01:47.401 --> 01:49.132
AND WHAT REASON
DID HE GIVE YOU?

01:49.134 --> 01:52.398
HE SUPPOSEDLY HAS A PROBLEM WITH
THE TAX BILL BEING A PERSONAL

01:52.400 --> 01:55.598
AND NOT AN INSTITUTIONAL DEBT,
BUT I'VE GOT A FUNNY FEELING

01:55.600 --> 01:58.532
THAT HE'S JUST HANGING
ONTO EVERY PENNY,

01:58.534 --> 02:02.798
THINKING THAT WHEN
CLARA DIES, HE'LL CASH IN.

02:02.800 --> 02:04.332
WHAT DID SHE SAY?

02:04.334 --> 02:06.798
THAT SHE HAD HEARD THAT YOU
AND I WERE HAVING TROUBLES

02:06.800 --> 02:08.865
AND SHE WOULDN'T FEEL
RIGHT DOWN THE ROAD

02:08.867 --> 02:11.598
SUPPORTING A CHURCH
WITH A DIVORCED BISHOP.

02:11.600 --> 02:13.065
WHO TOLD HER
WE'RE HAVING TROUBLES?

02:13.067 --> 02:16.998
WELL, SHE SAID CONNIE DID, BUT,
JAMES, EVERYBODY IS TALKING.

02:17.000 --> 02:20.065
LOOK, IT'S JUST MONEY.
I -- I'LL HANDLE IT.

02:20.067 --> 02:21.732
OH, LIKE YOU DID
THE LAST TIME?

02:21.734 --> 02:23.865
MAE, MAC WAS
YOUR BROTHER.

02:23.867 --> 02:25.199
HE'S THE ONE THAT GOT US
INTO THIS MESS.

02:25.201 --> 02:27.731
NO, YOU BOTH GOT US
INTO THIS MESS,

02:27.733 --> 02:29.198
AND MAC FAILED
TO GET US OUT.

02:29.200 --> 02:30.532
AND YOU WEREN'T
THERE EVERY WEEK

02:30.534 --> 02:32.198
WHEN WE COLLECTED
THOSE OFFERINGS,

02:32.200 --> 02:33.532
WHEN WE PAID
FOR THOSE CARS IN CASH.

02:33.534 --> 02:37.198
YOU TOLD ME THAT THOSE
OFFERINGS WERE NOT TAXABLE,

02:37.200 --> 02:38.198
AND I BELIEVED YOU.

02:38.200 --> 02:39.532
AND I BELIEVED MAC.

02:39.534 --> 02:42.199
OH, LOOK. EVERYBODY KNOWS
THAT WE'RE HAVING PROBLEMS,

02:42.201 --> 02:44.365
AND YOU HAVE TO DO
SOMETHING ABOUT IT.

02:44.367 --> 02:46.765
-LIKE WHAT?
-TELL THE CHURCH, LIKE ADULTS,

02:46.767 --> 02:48.432
THAT WE'RE
GETTING DIVORCED,

02:48.434 --> 02:53.765
AND THEN YOU'LL STEP ASIDE,
AND I'LL TAKE OVER.

02:53.767 --> 02:55.831
-EXCUSE ME?
-YOU HEARD ME.

02:55.833 --> 02:57.098
TAKE OVER WHAT?

02:57.100 --> 02:59.965
DON'T YOU DARE ACT LIKE YOU
DIDN'T KNOW WHEN YOU MET ME

02:59.967 --> 03:02.465
THAT I HAD A CALLING
ON MY LIFE FROM GOD,

03:02.467 --> 03:04.865
AND I DUMPED IT IN THE DIRT
AND FOLLOWED YOU,

03:04.867 --> 03:07.865
AND WHAT DID THAT GET ME?
-JANELLE AND TIFFANY.

03:07.867 --> 03:12.398
JAMES, STEP DOWN.
WALK AWAY.

03:12.400 --> 03:15.065
LET ME RAISE THE MONEY
FOR THE I.R.S.

03:15.067 --> 03:16.465
IT WON'T BE
YOUR PROBLEM.

03:16.467 --> 03:18.798
NOW, THAT IS MY OFFER,
AND YOU WON'T GET BETTER.

03:18.800 --> 03:22.465
I APPLAUD YOUR DESIRE TO
RECLAIM WHAT YOU LEFT BEHIND.

03:22.467 --> 03:25.398
I REALLY DO,
BUT SADLY,

03:25.400 --> 03:29.498
IT'S BASED ON
A SORELY MISTAKEN IDEA.

03:29.500 --> 03:35.799
IF WE DIVORCE, IT'S YOU WHO
WILL EXIT THE BUILDING, NOT ME.

03:40.067 --> 03:42.199
THAT'S NATURE'S WAY.

03:46.700 --> 03:48.332
♪ AMEN ♪

03:50.867 --> 03:52.132
♪ ALL RIGHT ♪

03:52.134 --> 03:53.332
♪ AMEN ♪

03:53.334 --> 03:56.465
♪ UH-HUH, HMM ♪

03:56.467 --> 03:58.865
♪ OOH-OOH, OOH ♪

04:02.000 --> 04:03.332
♪ WELL ♪

04:06.800 --> 04:09.732
♪ OH-OHH, OHH ♪

04:09.734 --> 04:15.332
♪ OOH, OOH, OOH, OOH ♪

04:15.334 --> 04:18.299
♪ AMEN, AMEN ♪
♪ OH ♪

04:21.800 --> 04:23.598
♪ YEAH ♪

04:23.600 --> 04:26.598
-- Captions by VITAC --
 www.vitac.com

04:26.600 --> 04:29.499
CAPTIONS PAID FOR BY
DISCOVERY COMMUNICATIONS

04:36.300 --> 04:39.432
[ DOOR KNOCKING ]

04:39.434 --> 04:40.898
YEAH.

04:40.900 --> 04:43.398
Mae: YES.

04:43.400 --> 04:46.331
YES?

04:46.333 --> 04:51.432
BIBLE STUDY IN 15 MINUTES.

04:51.434 --> 04:53.298
DID YOU HEAR ME?

04:53.300 --> 04:55.798
YES.

04:55.800 --> 04:57.932
Mae: THANK YOU.

04:57.934 --> 05:00.499
[ GROANING ]

05:04.467 --> 05:06.865
Mae: IT'S JUST THE HOPE
IN THIS PASSAGE.

05:06.867 --> 05:10.398
IT'S
SO INSPIRATIONAL.

05:10.400 --> 05:12.798
Sophia:
MORNING, ZORA.

05:12.800 --> 05:16.265
-ZORA?
-MORNING.

05:16.267 --> 05:19.499
-GOOD MORNING, GRANDMA.
-MORNING.

05:21.101 --> 05:23.299
-HAVE A GOOD RUN.
-THANK YOU.

05:25.367 --> 05:27.932
SO, ZORA, WHY DON'T YOU
READ THE NEXT VERSE?

05:33.400 --> 05:37.465
"FOR I HAVE
BRIEFLY ABANDONED YOU,

05:37.467 --> 05:42.131
BUT WITH DEEP COMPASSION,
I WILL BRING YOU BACK."

05:42.133 --> 05:47.932
AND HE WILL.
HE WILL BRING US BACK.

05:47.934 --> 05:57.998
♪♪

05:58.000 --> 06:07.998
♪♪

06:08.000 --> 06:17.998
♪♪

06:18.000 --> 06:28.165
♪♪

06:28.167 --> 06:38.065
♪♪

06:38.067 --> 06:40.665
[ DOOR KNOCKING ]

06:45.400 --> 06:50.598
-HEY. CAN I COME IN?
-WHAT DO YOU WANT?

06:50.600 --> 06:53.432
-JUST SEEING IF YOU'RE OKAY.
-WHY WOULDN'T I BE?

07:02.067 --> 07:04.132
DID KEVIN COME THIS MORNING
TO PICK UP NATHAN FOR THE WEEK?

07:04.134 --> 07:09.298
YEAH, AND HE WOULDN'T BE IF YOU
HAD JUST STAYED OUT OF IT.

07:09.300 --> 07:11.165
I ASKED HIM
NOT TO CALL THE POLICE.

07:11.167 --> 07:12.932
AND HE JUST
WOULDN'T LISTEN?

07:12.934 --> 07:15.732
I GOT ARRESTED AT
THE FOUR SEASONS, GRACE.

07:15.734 --> 07:17.732
AND I MADE SURE THAT
HE DIDN'T PRESS CHARGES.

07:17.734 --> 07:20.398
NOT BEFORE
I WAS IN HANDCUFFS.

07:20.400 --> 07:22.732
DO YOU HAVE ANY IDEA
HOW HUMILIATING...

07:22.734 --> 07:25.165
IF YOU'D JUST CALLED ME,
I COULD'VE COME AND GOT YOU.

07:25.167 --> 07:28.232
GET OUT!
GOD, LEAVE.

07:31.267 --> 07:32.165
I'M SORRY.

07:41.800 --> 07:46.899
HEY. HEY.

07:54.400 --> 07:59.299
OH! OW.

08:11.100 --> 08:12.532
KARINE?

08:12.534 --> 08:15.732
-GOOD MORNING, BISHOP.
-GET ME PERCY THOMPSON, PLEASE.

08:15.734 --> 08:16.665
RIGHT AWAY.

08:17.667 --> 08:19.865
BISHOP?

08:19.867 --> 08:21.865
I JUST WANT TO SAY
I'M SORRY ABOUT NANA

08:21.867 --> 08:24.065
NOT GIVING YOU
THE MONEY.

08:24.067 --> 08:26.999
DON'T BE SILLY.
GOD WILL PROVIDE.

08:30.667 --> 08:33.198
CAN'T WAIT
TO SEE HOW.

08:33.200 --> 08:34.198
WOW.

08:34.200 --> 08:35.865
JACOB HAS
TO SIGN ALL OF THESE?

08:35.867 --> 08:38.065
DO YOU HAVE
A PROBLEM WITH THAT?

08:38.067 --> 08:42.132
NO. UM,
WHAT ARE THEY?

08:42.134 --> 08:44.699
WELL, MOST OF THEM ARE JUST
A BUNCH OF LEGALESE NOTHING,

08:44.701 --> 08:48.698
BUT THERE IS A FORM IN
THERE THAT AUTHORIZES

08:48.700 --> 08:51.565
THE OPENING OF A BANK ACCOUNT
FOR THE REAL CHURCH.

08:51.567 --> 08:55.032
REAL? REAL CHURCH
DOESN'T EXIST ANYMORE.

08:55.034 --> 08:58.498
CHILD, LEAN OVER LIKE YOU KNOW
HOW AND GET HIM TO SIGNIN'.

08:58.500 --> 09:00.499
BELIEVE ME, HE WON'T
BE LOOKING DOWN.

09:02.867 --> 09:06.732
ALL RIGHT.
ARE YOU GOING TO CALVARY?

09:06.734 --> 09:09.132
AFTER THE WAY BISHOP TALKED
TO ME AT THAT ROUNDTABLE PARTY,

09:09.134 --> 09:11.198
HE GOING TO HAVE
TO LOOK FOR ME,

09:11.200 --> 09:14.732
AND WITH HIS I.R.S. TROUBLES
ALL OVER THE FRONT-PAGE NEWS,

09:14.734 --> 09:16.932
YOU CAN BET
YO' ASS HE IS.

09:22.467 --> 09:23.865
MAE, YOU WANTED
TO SEE ME?

09:23.867 --> 09:26.265
YES, PLEASE COME IN.
CLOSE THE DOOR.

09:36.000 --> 09:39.599
I AM SO CONCERNED AS I'M
SURE YOU ARE, CONNIE,

09:39.601 --> 09:44.131
ABOUT THIS I.R.S. SCANDAL,
BUT IT'S GOING TO BE OKAY.

09:44.133 --> 09:45.131
I HAVE NO DOUBT.

09:45.133 --> 09:47.565
-OH, PLEASE.
-THANK YOU.

09:49.000 --> 09:52.598
I'VE ALREADY SPOKEN TO
BISHOP ABOUT STEPPING ASIDE.

09:52.600 --> 09:56.832
HE HASN'T ASSENTED TO IT YET,
BUT I KNOW HE WILL BECAUSE HE,

09:56.834 --> 10:01.198
AS WELL AS YOU AND I, CONNIE,
WANT WHAT'S BEST FOR CALVARY.

10:01.200 --> 10:03.199
WELL, THIS IS SUCH
A RELIEF TO HEAR.

10:03.201 --> 10:09.165
AND THE GOOD NEWS IS, I AM
READY TO STEP UP AND TAKE OVER.

10:09.167 --> 10:11.831
MAE, WE'VE -- WE'VE HAD
THIS DISCUSSION BEFORE.

10:11.833 --> 10:15.531
WELL, THIS TIME
IT'S NOT A DISCUSSION.

10:15.533 --> 10:17.799
MAE, IT'S
MY FEELING,

10:17.801 --> 10:20.798
AND THE DEACON BOARD
SHARES THIS FEELING

10:20.800 --> 10:23.665
THAT THE BEST HOPE
FOR A STABLE FUTURE

10:23.667 --> 10:30.199
IS IF A DISINTERESTED THIRD
PARTY TAKES OVER THE PULPIT.

10:30.201 --> 10:34.098
AND WHO ON EARTH
WOULD BE DISINTERESTED?

10:34.100 --> 10:36.365
WHY, GRACE.

10:42.867 --> 10:43.865
Sophia: OKAY, WALK STRAIGHT
A COUPLE STEPS.

10:43.867 --> 10:46.765
OKAY, STOP.
TURN TO YOUR LEFT.

10:46.767 --> 10:49.565
YES. NOW KEEP GOING STRAIGHT.
KEEP GOING STRAIGHT.

10:49.567 --> 10:51.032
A LITTLE TO THE RIGHT,
A LITTLE TO THE RIGHT.

10:51.034 --> 10:54.798
OH, THERE WE GO. WE SAVED YOU.
NOW TURN AROUND.

10:54.800 --> 10:57.099
OKAY. SLOWLY SIT DOWN.

10:59.600 --> 11:00.532
GOOD JOB.

11:00.534 --> 11:04.531
[ APPLAUSE ]

11:04.533 --> 11:07.798
OKAY. SO THAT'S WHAT
IT MEANS TO HAVE FAITH.

11:07.800 --> 11:09.865
JUST LIKE GAVIN
TRUSTED ME TO LEAD HIM,

11:09.867 --> 11:11.999
WE TRUST GOD TO LEAD US,

11:12.001 --> 11:13.732
EVEN WHEN WE CAN'T SEE
WHERE WE'RE GOING,

11:13.734 --> 11:15.732
AND IT'S SUPER SCARY.
MAKE SENSE?

11:15.734 --> 11:16.932
All: MM-HMM.

11:16.934 --> 11:18.565
OKAY. GOOD.

11:18.567 --> 11:21.132
SO I WANT EVERYBODY
TO HELP CLEAN UP.

11:24.434 --> 11:26.165
HEY.

11:26.167 --> 11:29.265
HEY, STRANGER.

11:29.267 --> 11:30.465
YOU'RE SO GOOD
WITH THEM.

11:32.667 --> 11:35.932
I THINK THEY'RE
GOOD WITH ME.

11:35.934 --> 11:38.732
WHAT ARE YOU
DOING AFTER THIS?

11:38.734 --> 11:40.199
WHY?

11:40.201 --> 11:43.265
I WAS THINKING WE CAN
GRAB SOMETHING TO EAT.

11:43.267 --> 11:45.732
SOMEONE WANTS
TO APOLOGIZE?

11:45.734 --> 11:48.065
FOR STARTERS.

11:54.967 --> 11:57.299
SOUNDS LIKE YOU GOT
WHAT GIL SCOTT-HERON CALLS

11:57.301 --> 11:59.831
THE DOUBLE BLUES.
-WHAT'S THAT?

11:59.833 --> 12:04.565
OH, THAT'S THE, I-GOT-NO-
MONEY-NEITHER-NO-WOMAN BLUES.

12:04.567 --> 12:08.665
THAT'S NOT SO FUNNY WHEN
YOU ACTUALLY HAVE THOSE BLUES.

12:08.667 --> 12:10.265
YOU HAD SOME TROUBLE
WITH THE I.R.S.

12:10.267 --> 12:11.465
A FEW YEARS BACK,
DIDN'T YOU?

12:11.467 --> 12:12.998
INDEED I DID.

12:13.000 --> 12:15.865
ROLLED UP TO MY FUNERAL HOME
AND FOUND A PADLOCK ON THE DOOR

12:15.867 --> 12:19.132
AND A SIGN HOLLERING,
"NEGRO, GET ME MY MONEY."

12:19.134 --> 12:20.598
WELL, HOW'D
YOU HANDLE THAT?

12:20.600 --> 12:23.932
WELL, GOT ME A LAWYER,
ROBBED PETER TO PAY PAUL,

12:23.934 --> 12:27.732
BORROWED THIS, SOLD THAT,
DIDN'T OWE NO MILLIONS.

12:27.734 --> 12:31.665
WELL, THIS IS AS DEEP A HOLE
AS I DONE EVER BEEN IN,

12:31.667 --> 12:32.998
THAT'S FOR SURE.

12:33.000 --> 12:35.498
WELL, YOU GOT A WAY TO DIG
YOURSELF OUT OF THAT HOLE,

12:35.500 --> 12:37.332
YOU'RE JUST TOO SCARED
TO USE IT.

12:37.334 --> 12:39.565
-HOW YOU SAY THAT?
-OH, THAT PRETTY LITTLE BUNNY

12:39.567 --> 12:42.765
YOU HAD PRANCING
AROUND YOUR PARTY.

12:42.767 --> 12:44.898
MS. CROSS? YEAH.

12:44.900 --> 12:46.498
SO WHY ARE
YOU TALKING TO ME

12:46.500 --> 12:48.332
WHEN YOU NEED
TO BE TALKING TO HER?

12:48.334 --> 12:50.865
OH, PERCY,
THERE BE DRAGONS.

12:50.867 --> 12:54.465
THE THING ABOUT DRAGONS IS,
THEY GOT POTS OF GOLD,

12:54.467 --> 12:58.265
NOW, THAT WOMAN HANDLES MORE
THAN HEDGE FUNDS AND STOCKS.

12:58.267 --> 13:02.132
SHE'S INTO CRYPTOCURRENCY
AND APPARENTLY DOING QUITE WELL.

13:02.134 --> 13:03.065
CRYPTO WHAT?

13:03.067 --> 13:07.065
CRYPTOCURRENCY,
ZCOINS, BITCASH.

13:07.067 --> 13:09.398
-NEVER HEARD OF IT.
-WELL, IT'S A WHOLE NEW MARKET,

13:09.400 --> 13:11.999
AND IT'S GROWING FASTER
THAN BAD GRASS.

13:12.001 --> 13:13.965
HOW'D YOU HEAR
ABOUT IT?

13:13.967 --> 13:16.198
HER WEBSITE.

13:16.200 --> 13:17.732
WHAT YOU DOING
ON HER WEBSITE?

13:17.734 --> 13:19.699
AND WHAT DO YOU CARE?

13:19.701 --> 13:21.365
OH, JUST GIVE ME
THE LAWYER'S NUMBER.

13:21.367 --> 13:24.398
WELL, GET ME
HER NUMBER.

13:24.400 --> 13:26.099
YOU KNOW, YOU AIN'T
NOTHIN' BUT TROUBLE.

13:26.101 --> 13:27.365
YEAH, BUT GOOD TROUBLE.

13:27.367 --> 13:28.365
MM.

13:28.367 --> 13:31.232
HEY, PASTOR,
GOT A MINUTE?

13:31.234 --> 13:32.999
YEAH, SURE.
COME IN, TASHA.

13:37.800 --> 13:39.265
OH, SMART.

13:39.267 --> 13:41.932
-OH, I CAN COME BACK.
-NO, NO, NO.

13:41.934 --> 13:47.199
YOU'RE JUST IN TIME
TO WITNESS MY CRUSHING VICTORY.

13:47.201 --> 13:50.465
OKAY. WELL,
HEY THERE, HANDSOME.

13:50.467 --> 13:52.865
-THANK YOU.
[ BOTH LAUGH ]

13:52.867 --> 13:54.732
HE LOOKS
JUST LIKE YOU.

13:54.734 --> 13:57.698
YEAH, THAT'S WHAT
THEY TELL ME.

13:57.700 --> 13:59.365
ALL RIGHT.
THERE'S MY MOVE.

13:59.367 --> 14:00.332
WHAT'S YOUR MOVE?

14:02.567 --> 14:04.798
CHECKMATE.

14:04.800 --> 14:06.932
WHAT? IS THAT...

14:06.934 --> 14:10.399
ARE YOU KIDDING ME?
YOU SEE THAT?

14:10.401 --> 14:11.999
HOW DID YOU GET
TO BE SO SMART, HUH?

14:12.001 --> 14:14.332
YOU GET THOSE SMARTS
FROM ME, HUH?

14:14.334 --> 14:16.065
UM, YOU KNOW,
I SHOULD GO.

14:16.067 --> 14:17.499
NO, NO, NO. HOLD ON.
TASHA, IT'S COOL. HOLD ON.

14:17.501 --> 14:20.265
IS THAT FOR ME?
-OH, IT -- IT CAN WAIT.

14:20.267 --> 14:22.465
I MEAN, IT'S OKAY.
I MEAN, I CAN USE A WIN

14:22.467 --> 14:26.265
AFTER THE STOMPING I JUST TOOK
FROM THE LITTLE MASTER HERE.

14:26.267 --> 14:30.865
UM, I JUST...YOU KNOW,
IT'S THE SILLIEST THING.

14:30.867 --> 14:34.798
THE A/C IN MY OFFICE,
THE LITTLE VENTY THINGY,

14:34.800 --> 14:37.132
IT JUST BLOWS ON
FULL BLAST ALL THE TIME.

14:37.134 --> 14:38.099
OKAY.

14:38.101 --> 14:39.431
I TALKED TO CRAIG
IN THE MAINTENANCE

14:39.433 --> 14:41.165
ABOUT TURNING IT DOWN,
BUT...

14:41.167 --> 14:43.832
WELL, YOU KNOW WHAT?
I'LL GIVE HIM A CALL.

14:43.834 --> 14:45.965
WELL, I MEAN,
IF YOU SEE HIM.

14:45.967 --> 14:48.365
IT'S NOT A BIG DEAL.
-I'LL TAKE CARE OF IT.

14:49.567 --> 14:54.865
OKAY.
WELL, Y'ALL HAVE FUN, OKAY?

14:54.867 --> 14:57.132
-ALL RIGHT.
-ALL RIGHT.

14:57.134 --> 14:59.199
-BYE.
-BYE.

15:05.467 --> 15:07.699
WELL, GOOD AFTERNOON,
MAMA.

15:13.800 --> 15:18.898
SO I SPOKE TO CONNIE, AND I KNOW
ABOUT THIS LITTLE COUP OF YOURS.

15:18.900 --> 15:20.198
COUP?

15:20.200 --> 15:21.965
YOU SPOKE TO HER
ABOUT TAKING OVER?

15:21.967 --> 15:23.965
SHE SPOKE TO ME.
I SAID NO.

15:23.967 --> 15:25.332
WELL,
HOW CONCLUSIVELY,

15:25.334 --> 15:27.732
BECAUSE SHE SEEMS TO THINK
THAT YOU'RE STILL AVAILABLE.

15:27.734 --> 15:28.998
AND I'LL
TELL HER AGAIN.

15:29.000 --> 15:29.965
IF YOUR FATHER
EVER KNEW

15:29.967 --> 15:32.065
THAT YOU WERE CONSPIRING
WITH CONNIE

15:32.067 --> 15:34.231
TO STEAL HIS CHURCH
FROM UNDERNEATH HIM...

15:34.233 --> 15:35.832
HE'D BE MISINFORMED.

15:37.534 --> 15:38.865
FOR YOUR
INFORMATION, MAMA,

15:38.867 --> 15:41.665
YOU TWO ARE LOSING THIS
CHURCH ALL ON YOUR OWN.

15:41.667 --> 15:45.931
YOU WANT CONNIE OFF YOUR BACKS?
FORGIVE EACH OTHER AND MOVE ON.

15:45.933 --> 15:47.931
PUT AN END
TO ALL THE RUMORS. LEAD.

15:47.933 --> 15:49.665
DON'T YOU THINK
THAT IF I COULD

15:49.667 --> 15:52.932
PUT THIS MESS BACK
TOGETHER, I WOULD?

15:52.934 --> 15:55.865
DO YOU HONESTLY THINK THAT I
WOULD CUT OFF MY OWN NOSE

15:55.867 --> 15:59.598
TO SPITE MY FACE WITH SO MUCH
ON THE LINE, OUR WHOLE FAMILY?

15:59.600 --> 16:02.865
I DON'T KNOW. I DON'T KNOW
WHERE THE PRIDE ENDS

16:02.867 --> 16:06.798
AND THE WEAKNESS BEGINS
WITH YOU TWO ANYMORE.

16:06.800 --> 16:09.798
I DON'T WANT
THE CHURCH.

16:09.800 --> 16:13.732
GOOD BECAUSE
YOU'LL NEVER GET IT.

16:13.734 --> 16:21.098
♪♪

16:21.100 --> 16:28.332
♪♪

16:28.334 --> 16:35.831
♪♪

16:35.833 --> 16:43.132
♪♪

16:43.134 --> 16:46.465
[ DOOR OPENS, SLAMS ]

16:46.467 --> 16:54.465
♪♪

17:00.600 --> 17:04.765
-IS EVERYTHING OKAY?
-YOU TELL ME.

17:04.767 --> 17:07.665
I'M JUST WAITING ON THAT
ACCOUNT AUTHORIZATION FORM.

17:07.667 --> 17:10.598
OH, YEAH, UM...

17:10.600 --> 17:12.898
YOU COULDN'T
GET HIM TO SIGN IT?

17:12.900 --> 17:14.432
NO, I JUST, UM...

17:16.334 --> 17:18.332
YOU KNOW, IT REALLY WASN'T
THE RIGHT TIME.

17:18.334 --> 17:20.798
DO YOU WANT TO SEE
BASIE AGAIN?

17:20.800 --> 17:23.065
-OF COURSE I DO.
-THEN MAKE IT THE RIGHT TIME.

17:24.334 --> 17:26.465
BECAUSE UNTIL WE CAN START
SHIFTING MONEY

17:26.467 --> 17:30.798
INTO THAT ACCOUNT, WE HAVE
NOTHING ON HIM OR BISHOP.

17:30.800 --> 17:33.799
AND YOU AND BASIE
AIN'T EVER TRIUMPH BACK.

17:33.801 --> 17:35.399
UNDERSTAND?

17:35.401 --> 17:38.132
YEAH. I'LL GET HIM
TO SIGN THEM TOMORROW.

17:38.134 --> 17:39.299
DO.

17:46.567 --> 17:51.065
MS. CONNIE,
YOU SPOKE TO MY MOTHER.

17:51.067 --> 17:52.532
I ASSUME
SHE SPOKE TO YOU.

17:52.534 --> 17:54.998
SHE DID.

17:55.000 --> 17:56.732
LOOK, I KNOW
YOU'RE UP AGAINST IT.

17:56.734 --> 17:58.532
WE ALL ARE,

17:58.534 --> 18:00.932
BUT I'M NOT SURE MY TAKING OVER
THE CHURCH IS THE RIGHT THING.

18:00.934 --> 18:04.431
LAST SUMMER, WHEN I PREACHED,
THE OFFERING ACTUALLY WENT DOWN,

18:04.433 --> 18:05.899
AND YOU AND I BOTH KNOW
THAT MY POLITICS

18:05.901 --> 18:08.598
AREN'T EXACTLY IN TUNE WITH
YOU AND THE DEACON BOARD.

18:08.600 --> 18:12.898
WELL, I THOUGHT WE MIGHT BE ABLE
TO FIND A MIDDLE GROUND,

18:12.900 --> 18:17.165
THAT IS, IF BY POLITICS,
YOU MEAN OPEN AND INCLUSIVE.

18:17.167 --> 18:20.132
THERE IS NO MIDDLE GROUND
WITH OPEN AND INCLUSIVE,

18:20.134 --> 18:22.465
BUT IT'S MORE THAN THAT.
IF I TAKE OVER,

18:22.467 --> 18:24.532
I'M GONNA WANT TO MOVE
THIS CHURCH FORWARD.

18:24.534 --> 18:26.465
TO A PLACE THEY MAY
NOT BE READY TO GO.

18:28.867 --> 18:30.998
ARE YOU REALLY WILLING
TO JUST STAND BY

18:31.000 --> 18:33.931
AND WATCH
THIS CHURCH DIE?

18:33.933 --> 18:38.865
FIRST OF ALL, I'M NOT STANDING
BY AND WATCHING ANYTHING DIE.

18:38.867 --> 18:42.198
I AM ON MY KNEES, DAY AND NIGHT,
PRAYING THAT MY PARENTS

18:42.200 --> 18:44.198
WILL FIND A WAY
TO WORK THROUGH THIS

18:44.200 --> 18:47.031
OR THAT GOD WILL WORK IT OUT.
-I PRAY FOR THAT AS WELL.

18:47.033 --> 18:48.965
AND NO, I'M NOT WILLING
TO MARCH IN PLACE

18:48.967 --> 18:50.098
AND CALL IT PROGRESS
JUST TO KEEP

18:50.100 --> 18:53.298
THE GREENLEAF NAME
ON A LETTERHEAD.

18:53.300 --> 18:57.299
THAT'S NOT CHURCH.
-AND WHAT IS CHURCH TO YOU?

18:57.301 --> 19:08.632
JESUS' WAY, LOVE, UNCONDITIONAL
LOVE, AND CHANGE.

19:08.634 --> 19:13.065
WELL, CHANGE IS
COMING.

19:13.067 --> 19:14.532
YOUR MOTHER HAS
IT IN HER HEAD

19:14.534 --> 19:17.565
TO TRY AND STAY ON
AFTER THE DIVORCE.

19:19.334 --> 19:23.065
WHAT PLANET SHE HEARD
THAT WORKS ON, I DON'T KNOW.

19:23.067 --> 19:26.398
I LOOK AHEAD AND I
SEE SCHISM, SCANDAL,

19:26.400 --> 19:30.665
AND A BIG OLE
FOR-SALE SIGN OUT FRONT.

19:30.667 --> 19:35.465
THAT'LL BE CHANGE, ALL RIGHT,
BUT IT WON'T BE CHURCH.

19:41.400 --> 19:51.365
♪♪

19:51.367 --> 19:53.099
HMM.

19:53.101 --> 19:56.632
BISHOP GREENLEAF,
AS I LIVE AND BREATHE.

19:56.634 --> 19:59.832
I NEVER WOULD'VE EXPECTED YOU
TO DARKEN MY DOORSTEP AGAIN.

19:59.834 --> 20:03.798
DID YOU COME TO CHIDE ME
FOR NOT COMING TO SERVICE TODAY?

20:03.800 --> 20:05.732
I FEEL BAD ABOUT HOW WE
LEFT THINGS AT THE PARTY.

20:05.734 --> 20:08.732
I CAME TO OFFER
MY SINCEREST APOLOGY.

20:08.734 --> 20:11.132
HMM.
IS THAT ALL?

20:11.134 --> 20:14.065
NO, YOU --
YOU WERE RIGHT.

20:14.067 --> 20:17.332
I HAVE BEEN INCONSISTENT
IN MY RESPONSES TO YOU,

20:17.334 --> 20:19.198
AND, OF COURSE,
YOU FELT USED.

20:19.200 --> 20:23.865
WHO COULD BLAME YOU?
I HOPE YOU CAN FORGIVE ME.

20:23.867 --> 20:25.798
WELL, I'M A CHRISTIAN WOMAN
FIRST AND FOREMOST,

20:25.800 --> 20:28.865
SO YES,
I DO FORGIVE YOU.

20:28.867 --> 20:30.132
THANK YOU.

20:30.134 --> 20:33.398
IS THAT ALL
YOU CAME TO SAY?

20:33.400 --> 20:35.398
WELL, I COULD USE
A LITTLE ADVICE.

20:35.400 --> 20:37.665
ABOUT?

20:37.667 --> 20:41.398
THIS I.R.S. MESS.

20:41.400 --> 20:43.465
YOU'VE READ
THE PAPER, I ASSUME?

20:43.467 --> 20:45.665
-ME AND EVERYONE ELSE.
-INDEED.

20:45.667 --> 20:50.132
YOU KNOW, WE THOUGHT WE HAD
IT COVERED, BUT WE DON'T.

20:50.134 --> 20:53.265
I DIDN'T WANT TO BOTHER YOU,
BUT I PRAYED ON IT, AND I...

20:53.267 --> 20:56.232
YOU PRAYED, AND IT BROUGHT
YOU BACK TO THIS JEZEBEL?

20:56.234 --> 20:58.032
IS THAT HOW
YOUR JESUS WORKS?

20:58.034 --> 20:59.498
YOU JUST SHOW UP AND SAY,
"I'M SORRY,"

20:59.500 --> 21:01.598
AND I'M SUPPOSED TO WHIP
UP SOME CASH FOR YOU?

21:01.600 --> 21:03.465
HA!
BRUH.

21:03.467 --> 21:06.798
IT WASN'T LIKE THAT.
I THOUGHT YOU WANTED TO HELP.

21:06.800 --> 21:07.865
I...

21:07.867 --> 21:12.332
NOW, WHY WOULD
I WANT TO HELP YOU?

21:12.334 --> 21:14.565
NO.

21:19.267 --> 21:22.732
YOU'RE RIGHT.
I'M SORRY.

21:22.734 --> 21:24.198
YOU JUST CAN'T THROW ME
OUT ON THE STREET

21:24.200 --> 21:26.598
AND COME BACK
BEGGING FOR FAVORS.

21:26.600 --> 21:31.465
IF HE COMES BACK CALLING AGAIN,
FRED, DON'T TELL ME.

21:31.467 --> 21:33.665
I DON'T
WANT TO KNOW.

21:33.667 --> 21:43.265
♪♪

21:43.267 --> 21:52.865
♪♪

21:52.867 --> 22:02.398
♪♪

22:02.400 --> 22:11.998
♪♪

22:12.000 --> 22:21.999
♪♪

22:30.867 --> 22:33.465
Sophia: YOU'VE BEEN
DOING SOME DIGGING.

22:36.934 --> 22:41.198
-YOU TAKING IT BACK, HUH?
-MY IPOD WAS CONFISCATED.

22:41.200 --> 22:42.865
I JUST WENT THROUGH
FAITH'S OLD STUFF,

22:42.867 --> 22:46.998
AND NOW I'M VIBING OUT TO SOME
ICE-T, PRE-"LAW & ORDER."

22:47.000 --> 22:49.465
I DIDN'T EVEN KNOW THERE WAS
A PRE-"LAW & ORDER" ICE-T.

22:49.467 --> 22:50.765
SIGN ME UP.

22:55.134 --> 22:57.132
WANT TO GO TO ZAXBY'S?

23:03.067 --> 23:07.332
WANT TO GO TO ZAXBY'S?
-I'D RATHER EAT MY SOCKS.

23:07.334 --> 23:08.965
YOU KNOW, I DON'T WANT TO
ESPECIALLY HANG OUT

23:08.967 --> 23:12.099
WITH YOU EITHER.
I'M JUST TRYING TO BE NICE.

23:17.500 --> 23:19.465
-WHAT'S THE MATTER WITH YOU?
-NOTHING.

23:19.467 --> 23:23.498
I JUST KEEP GETTING
THIS PAIN IN MY SIDE.

23:23.500 --> 23:25.665
MAYBE YOU'RE
PREGNANT.

23:35.134 --> 23:38.332
[ CRYING, HEAVY BREATHING ]

23:38.334 --> 23:41.998
ARE YOU SURE
YOU DON'T WANT TO?

23:42.000 --> 23:43.532
-TAKE OVER CALVARY?
-MM-HMM.

23:43.534 --> 23:45.765
YEAH.

23:45.767 --> 23:48.099
SOME CHURCH SOMEDAY?

23:48.101 --> 23:52.998
MAYBE. WOULD YOU WANT
TO BE FIRST GENTLEMAN?

23:53.000 --> 23:55.065
OH.
-IS THAT WHAT THEY CALL IT?

23:55.067 --> 23:58.132
MM-HMM. FIRST LADY,
FIRST GENTLEMAN.

23:58.134 --> 24:02.631
HUH, I DON'T KNOW. I COULDN'T
BE FIRST BOYFRIEND?

24:02.633 --> 24:04.699
NOT IN ANY CHURCH
I'D BE RUNNING.

24:04.701 --> 24:09.365
NO, THEY WOULDN'T HAVE IT,
AND, REALLY, NEITHER WOULD I.

24:09.367 --> 24:11.532
THAT'S
GOOD TO KNOW.

24:11.534 --> 24:13.732
[ CELLPHONE RINGING ]

24:13.734 --> 24:15.798
MM.
THAT'S MY MOTHER.

24:15.800 --> 24:21.032
[ CELLPHONE RINGING CONTINUES ]

24:21.034 --> 24:25.165
OKAY. SHE'S JUST CALLING
TO YELL AT ME.

24:28.267 --> 24:29.965
HELLO?

24:37.633 --> 24:46.265
♪♪

24:46.267 --> 24:47.665
HI.

24:47.667 --> 24:50.865
HERE, YOU ACKNOWLEDGE THIS
IS AN EXPLORATORY LAPAROTOMY,

24:50.867 --> 24:53.065
AND YOU CONSENT TO TREATMENT
FOR CONDITIONS

24:53.067 --> 24:54.565
DISCOVERED
DURING SURGERY.

24:57.000 --> 24:58.732
PERFECT. THANK YOU.
-THANK YOU.

24:58.734 --> 25:00.065
WE'RE GONNA HAVE
THE NURSES COME IN

25:00.067 --> 25:01.632
AND PREP YOU
FOR SURGERY NOW.

25:03.800 --> 25:05.198
I'M SCARED.

25:05.200 --> 25:08.065
IT'S GONNA BE
ALL RIGHT, SWEETHEART.

25:08.067 --> 25:09.465
WILL YOU
STAY WITH ME?

25:09.467 --> 25:10.598
AFTER WE GET YOU PREPPED,

25:10.600 --> 25:12.232
SHE CAN COME BACK IN
AND SIT WITH YOU.

25:14.067 --> 25:16.932
I'M GONNA BE
RIGHT DOWN THE HALL.

25:16.934 --> 25:19.732
I LOVE YOU.
-I LOVE YOU.

25:19.734 --> 25:27.665
♪♪

25:27.667 --> 25:35.565
♪♪

25:35.567 --> 25:36.798
ANY WORD?

25:36.800 --> 25:39.398
SHE HAS
AN OVARIAN TORSION.

25:39.400 --> 25:41.231
THEY'RE GONNA UNTWIST IT, TRY
TO FIGURE OUT WHAT CAUSED IT.

25:41.233 --> 25:42.365
OH, MY LORD.

25:42.367 --> 25:47.598
POOR BABY. BEING SLICED
OPEN IS NOT FUN.

25:47.600 --> 25:50.732
SPEAKING FROM EXPERIENCE.
-HAVE YOU BEEN DRINKING?

25:50.734 --> 25:54.265
NO.
I HAD A LITTLE WINE,

25:54.267 --> 25:56.965
BUT, GIGI, I KNOW WHAT IT'S
LIKE TO LOSE A DAUGHTER,

25:56.967 --> 26:00.932
SO IF THIS THING GOES SOUTH,
JUST KNOW I GOT YOU.

26:00.934 --> 26:02.798
LISTEN, WHY DON'T WE
JUST SIT DOWN, HUH?

26:02.800 --> 26:04.065
I DON'T WANT
TO SIT.

26:04.067 --> 26:07.265
I WANT TO HELP GIGI
THROUGH HER GRIEF.

26:07.267 --> 26:10.632
-WE'RE READY FOR YOU, MOM.
-THANK YOU. OKAY.

26:12.434 --> 26:14.565
WHERE DO YOU THINK
YOU'RE GOING?

26:14.567 --> 26:15.865
I'M COMING
WITH YOU.

26:15.867 --> 26:18.832
I'M GOOD.
THANK YOU.

26:22.067 --> 26:26.665
THAT'S WHAT SHE DO.
SHE RUINS EVERYTHING.

26:26.667 --> 26:29.332
PLEASE DRINK
SOME WATER.

26:29.334 --> 26:32.099
I'M JUST TRYING
TO HELP, MAMA.

26:41.133 --> 26:46.532
-HEY.
-IT'S ALL GONNA BE OKAY.

26:46.534 --> 26:48.065
SHE'S ON SOMETHING,
I ASSUME?

26:48.067 --> 26:51.598
MM-HMM. I'M ON
A LOT OF SOMETHING.

26:51.600 --> 26:53.798
OH, CONGRATULATIONS.

26:53.800 --> 26:57.265
[ LAUGHS ]
YOU WANNA PRAY, BABY?

26:57.267 --> 27:00.398
NO. I WANT TO
TELL YOU A SECRET.

27:00.400 --> 27:04.065
ROBERTO WANTS TO MARRY ME.
-HE SAID THAT?

27:04.067 --> 27:08.798
-MM-HMM. YEAH, TODAY AT LUNCH.
-HE PROPOSED TO YOU?

27:08.800 --> 27:11.865
NO, BUT HE APOLOGIZED
FOR A FIGHT

27:11.867 --> 27:13.798
WE HAD THE OTHER NIGHT...
-AH.

27:13.800 --> 27:16.865
...AND SAID THAT HE RESPECTS
ME FOR SETTING BOUNDARIES,

27:16.867 --> 27:19.565
AND HE COULD SEE
A FUTURE. [ LAUGHS ]

27:19.567 --> 27:22.498
THAT'S WONDERFUL
HE LOVES YOU LIKE THAT,

27:22.500 --> 27:25.932
THAT YOU LOVE EACH OTHER.
-YEAH, AND A FUTURE.

27:25.934 --> 27:27.465
THAT'S GREAT.

27:27.467 --> 27:32.398
WE'RE GONNA GET MARRIED
WITH A BIG WEDDING AND A HOUSE

27:32.400 --> 27:36.699
AND A MAILBOX AND A PUPPY
AND KIDS AND...

27:39.633 --> 27:41.831
Nurse: WE'RE GONNA
TAKE HER IN NOW.

27:41.833 --> 27:50.198
♪♪

27:50.200 --> 27:58.565
♪♪

27:58.567 --> 28:05.631
[ CELLPHONE RINGING ]

28:05.633 --> 28:09.098
EXCUSE ME. CAN YOU TELL ME
WHERE THE CHAPEL IS?

28:09.100 --> 28:12.532
OH, IT'S RIGHT DOWN THE HALL
TO THE RIGHT.

28:12.534 --> 28:14.198
THANK YOU.

28:14.200 --> 28:23.832
♪♪

28:23.834 --> 28:26.398
SO HOW'S EVERYTHING GOING
AT YOUR GRANDMOTHER'S?

28:26.400 --> 28:28.732
IT'S FINE, I GUESS.
I'VE BEEN GAINING WEIGHT,

28:28.734 --> 28:30.932
AND IT'S ONLY BEEN,
LIKE, A WEEK,

28:30.934 --> 28:33.398
BUT THICK IS
KIND OF IN.

28:33.400 --> 28:37.465
-YOU LOOK GREAT, BABY.
-WHATEVER. IT'S FINE.

28:37.467 --> 28:39.065
HOW'S THINGS
GOING FOR YOU GUYS?

28:39.067 --> 28:43.732
I BET IT'S NICE AND QUIET
WITHOUT THE JUVENILE DELINQUENT.

28:43.734 --> 28:45.265
NOW, WHY YOU WANT
TO ACT LIKE THAT, HUH?

28:45.267 --> 28:49.032
YOU KICKED ME OUT OF THE HOUSE.
HOW ELSE AM I SUPPOSED TO ACT?

28:49.034 --> 28:52.965
PRINCESS, YOU TOLD US YOU DIDN'T
WANT TO LIVE THERE ANYMORE.

28:52.967 --> 28:54.265
YOU KNOW, THIS IS WHY
I DIDN'T WANT TO TALK,

28:54.267 --> 28:56.665
YOU'RE ALWAYS PICKING
AT ME ALL THE TIME.

28:56.667 --> 29:00.465
-HI. HOW'S SOPHIA?
-SHE'S IN SURGERY NOW.

29:00.467 --> 29:02.765
OH, OKAY.

29:08.334 --> 29:10.532
HEY, HONEY.

29:10.534 --> 29:13.265
HOW YOU DOIN'?
-FANTASTIC.

29:13.267 --> 29:17.065
EARLY-MORNING BIBLE STUDY,
NO T.V., NO COMPUTER.

29:17.067 --> 29:21.732
YOU KNOW, I'M TURNING INTO
A REGULAR AMERICAN GIRL DOLL.

29:21.734 --> 29:24.532
WASN'T THAT THE PLAN?

29:24.534 --> 29:26.831
IF YOU WANT TO COME HOME,
COME HOME, OKAY?

29:26.833 --> 29:28.399
YOU CAN COME HOME.

29:29.767 --> 29:31.565
[ HEAVY SIGH ]
I'LL BE GOOD.

29:35.967 --> 29:37.732
Y'ALL REALLY
MESSED HER UP BAD.

29:37.734 --> 29:38.798
EXCUSE ME?

29:38.800 --> 29:40.732
OH, DON'T GET MAD.
YOU GOT WINKIE.

29:40.734 --> 29:43.132
YOU CAN STILL HAVE
AT LEAST ONE GOOD KID.

29:43.134 --> 29:46.265
[ LAUGHS ]
-ARE YOU OKAY?

29:46.267 --> 29:48.598
WHY IS EVERYBODY
ASKING ME THAT?

29:48.600 --> 29:51.765
I'M FINE. EVERYBODY
NEEDS TO CHILL.

30:05.467 --> 30:09.232
OH, COME ON.
HAND IT OVER.

30:10.667 --> 30:12.265
[ POUNDING ]

30:12.267 --> 30:13.998
CHARITY,
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

30:14.000 --> 30:15.332
IT WON'T LET GO OF MY
WHATCHAMACALLIT.

30:15.334 --> 30:16.398
YOUR WHAT?

30:16.400 --> 30:19.465
MY WHATCHAMACALLIT,
MY CANDY BAR.

30:19.467 --> 30:21.932
OKAY. HERE, LET ME
GET YOU ANOTHER DOLLAR.

30:21.934 --> 30:23.632
[ BANGING ]

30:23.634 --> 30:25.132
WHAT IS
YOUR PROBLEM?

30:25.134 --> 30:27.798
I'M GETTING RIPPED OFF,
BUT YOU PICKED THE WRONG ONE.

30:27.800 --> 30:29.732
NOT TODAY, HONEY.
GIVE ME MY CANDY BAR.

30:29.734 --> 30:30.865
-CHARITY.
-IS SHE DRUNK?

30:30.867 --> 30:32.465
I DON'T KNOW.
IT SEEMS LIKE IT.

30:32.467 --> 30:33.465
-CHARITY...
-CHARITY, CALM DOWN.

30:33.467 --> 30:34.299
...HERE. HERE'S ANOTHER DOLLAR.

30:34.301 --> 30:35.765
I DON'T WANT MORE MONEY!

30:35.767 --> 30:38.632
I WANT WHAT I DESERVE!
I WANT MY CANDY BAR! AH!

30:38.634 --> 30:41.398
[ GLASS BREAKING ]

30:41.400 --> 30:47.798
♪♪

30:47.800 --> 30:49.099
OH, MY GOD.

30:51.367 --> 30:55.565
-CAN WE GET A NURSE?
-I'M GONNA NEED STITCHES.

30:57.434 --> 30:59.565
SOMEBODY GONNA
NEED A LAWYER.

31:36.134 --> 31:45.398
♪♪

31:45.400 --> 31:48.132
WHAT IS SHE ON?
DID THEY SAY?

31:48.134 --> 31:50.865
OXYCODONE.

31:50.867 --> 31:53.398
WHERE DID
SHE GET IT?

31:53.400 --> 31:56.198
LEFT OVER
FROM HER CESAREAN.

31:56.200 --> 31:58.665
OH. LOOK, MAE.

32:01.134 --> 32:05.398
LOOK, THESE KIDS
NEED THEIR PARENTS.

32:05.400 --> 32:09.198
I MEAN,
GRACE, CHARITY,

32:09.200 --> 32:16.598
JACOB WITH THIS ZORA MESS,
THEY ALL NEED US.

32:16.600 --> 32:19.832
WHAT ARE YOU
PROPOSING, JAMES?

32:19.834 --> 32:24.131
PLEASE, LET'S PUT
THIS BEHIND US.

32:24.133 --> 32:26.765
I WISH I COULD,
BUT I DON'T SEE HOW.

32:29.334 --> 32:31.532
I'VE REACHED A POINT
IN MY HEART

32:31.534 --> 32:38.532
WHERE GOING BACK WOULD BE AN ACT
OF DISRESPECT TO GOD HIMSELF.

32:46.400 --> 32:49.732
I'M SORRY.
I WISH IT COULD BE ANOTHER WAY,

32:49.734 --> 32:53.199
BUT IT'S TIME
TO TELL THE CHILDREN,

32:53.201 --> 32:56.065
THE CHURCH,
AND MOVE ON.

32:56.067 --> 32:58.198
Charity:
WHAT HAPPENED?

32:58.200 --> 33:00.865
Mae: YOU GOT UPSET
ABOUT A CANDY BAR.

33:03.533 --> 33:06.398
JAMES,
YOU'RE NOT WRONG.

33:06.400 --> 33:10.732
THESE CHILDREN DO NEED
THEIR MOTHER AND THEIR FATHER,

33:12.867 --> 33:16.132
BUT I DON'T THINK THEY'LL EVER
HAVE THEIR PARENTS AGAIN.

33:20.933 --> 33:24.465
NO, I CAN WALK, MAMA.
OH!

33:24.467 --> 33:25.998
MY HEAD HURTS.

33:26.000 --> 33:28.732
I'M SURE IT DOES.
I'M SURE THAT'S TRUE.

33:28.734 --> 33:29.999
OH!

33:31.134 --> 33:36.299
ALL RIGHT, BABY.
THAT'S ALL RIGHT, BABY.

33:39.067 --> 33:44.998
JAMES.
JAMES.

33:45.000 --> 33:52.665
♪♪

33:52.667 --> 34:00.398
♪♪

34:00.400 --> 34:08.132
♪♪

34:08.134 --> 34:16.065
♪♪

34:16.067 --> 34:17.899
[ DOOR OPENS ]

34:17.901 --> 34:26.598
♪♪

34:26.600 --> 34:35.198
♪♪

34:35.200 --> 34:43.865
♪♪

34:43.867 --> 34:53.632
-OUR FATHER WHO ART IN HEAVEN...
-HALLOWED BE THY NAME.

34:53.634 --> 34:56.365
THY KINGDOM COME.

34:56.367 --> 35:05.499
-THY WILL BE DONE,
-ON EARTH AS IT IS IN HEAVEN.

35:05.501 --> 35:12.665
All:
GIVE US THIS DAY OUR DAILY BREAD
AND FORGIVE US OUR TRESPASSES

35:12.667 --> 35:17.998
AS WE FORGIVE THOSE
WHO TRESPASS AGAINST US,

35:18.000 --> 35:23.865
AND LEAD US NOT INTO TEMPTATION
BUT DELIVER US FROM EVIL.

35:23.867 --> 35:25.932
[ CELLPHONE BUZZING ]

35:25.934 --> 35:27.332
FOR THINE IS THE KINGDOM,

35:27.334 --> 35:33.799
THE POWER AND THE GLORY
FOREVER AND EVER.

35:33.801 --> 35:35.199
AMEN.

35:35.201 --> 35:43.099
♪♪

35:48.400 --> 35:51.532
HEY. HOW DID IT GO?

35:51.534 --> 35:52.865
DURING THE SURGERY,

35:52.867 --> 35:55.265
WE DISCOVERED THE
CAUSE OF THE TORSION.

35:59.867 --> 36:03.465
SOPHIA HAD DERMOID CYSTS
ON BOTH OVARIES.

36:05.334 --> 36:06.665
IS THAT A CANCER?

36:06.667 --> 36:09.598
NO, THEY'RE TYPICALLY BENIGN
CYSTS THAT DEVELOP IN UTERO.

36:09.600 --> 36:11.365
THEY'RE
KIND OF STRANGE.

36:11.367 --> 36:14.365
THEY CAN BE FULL OF STRANGE
THINGS, LIKE HAIR OR TEETH.

36:14.367 --> 36:16.498
IN SOPHIA'S CASE,
THEY HAD GROWN QUITE LARGE

36:16.500 --> 36:19.798
AND WERE CAUSING SIGNIFICANT
ORGAN DISPLACEMENT AND NECROSIS,

36:19.800 --> 36:21.565
AND ONCE WE REMOVED THEM,

36:21.567 --> 36:22.632
THERE WASN'T ENOUGH
HEALTHY TISSUE

36:22.634 --> 36:25.265
LEFT TO PRESERVE THE OVARIES.

36:25.267 --> 36:31.932
SO YOU --
YOU TOOK THEM OUT?

36:31.934 --> 36:33.365
WE HAD NO CHOICE.

36:40.267 --> 36:45.865
OH. SHE'S NOT GOING
TO HAVE CHILDREN.

36:45.867 --> 36:49.932
NOT OF HER OWN.
I'M SORRY.

36:49.934 --> 36:56.732
♪♪

36:56.734 --> 37:03.798
♪♪

37:03.800 --> 37:10.598
♪♪

37:10.600 --> 37:13.265
PASTOR, I JUST HAVE
A FEW PAPERS HERE

37:13.267 --> 37:14.598
THAT NEED
YOUR JOHN HANCOCK.

37:14.600 --> 37:18.598
ALL RIGHT.
AND WHAT IS THIS?

37:18.600 --> 37:20.265
OH, SAME OLD,
SAME OLD.

37:20.267 --> 37:21.931
PAYROLL APPROVAL
AND PURCHASE ORDERS

37:21.933 --> 37:24.398
FOR THE STREAMING CAMERAS.
BLAH, BLAH, BLAH.

37:24.400 --> 37:25.932
ALL RIGHT.

37:25.934 --> 37:29.265
YOU KNOW, TASHA, IF I HAVEN'T
SAID SO ENOUGH ALREADY,

37:29.267 --> 37:30.998
THANK YOU SO MUCH
FOR STEPPING UP AROUND HERE.

37:31.000 --> 37:31.998
OH.

37:32.000 --> 37:33.398
SPENT THE NIGHT
IN THE HOSPITAL

37:33.400 --> 37:35.265
WITH SOPHIA
AND CHARITY.

37:35.267 --> 37:36.798
-OH, NO. ARE THEY OKAY?
-YEAH.

37:36.800 --> 37:39.398
THANKFULLY YES,
BUT I DON'T KNOW.

37:39.400 --> 37:42.532
I MEAN, BETWEEN ZORA
BEING A HANDFUL,

37:42.534 --> 37:46.231
KERISSA STRETCHED SUPER THIN
OVER AT HER SCHOOL...

37:46.233 --> 37:48.031
I MEAN, I DON'T KNOW, US TRYING
TO GET OUR STREAMING UP

37:48.033 --> 37:51.631
AND RUNNING,
IT'S JUST SUPER APPRECIATED

37:51.633 --> 37:53.432
HOW MUCH HELP
YOU'VE BEEN.

37:53.434 --> 37:56.398
-OH, IT AIN'T NO THING.
-OH, NO.

37:56.400 --> 38:00.998
IT IS A THING,
AND I TOLD CRAIG

38:01.000 --> 38:02.332
NOT ONLY TO TURN UP
THE HEAT IN YOUR OFFICE,

38:02.334 --> 38:05.398
BUT IF YOU EVER,
IF YOU EVER ASK FOR ANYTHING,

38:05.400 --> 38:07.065
AND YOU DON'T GET IT
IMMEDIATELY,

38:07.067 --> 38:08.798
HE'S GOING TO BE
LOOKING FOR WORK.

38:08.800 --> 38:10.332
YOU DID NOT
HAVE TO DO THAT.

38:10.334 --> 38:14.398
OH, YES I DID.
YOU KNOW WHY?

38:14.400 --> 38:15.665
BECAUSE YOU'RE FAMILY.

38:18.000 --> 38:20.565
-THANK YOU.
-THANK YOU.

38:23.700 --> 38:26.065
AND JUST...
YEP.

38:26.067 --> 38:28.032
ALL RIGHT.

38:28.500 --> 38:34.265
♪♪

38:34.267 --> 38:38.098
[ DOOR OPENS, CLOSES ]

38:38.100 --> 38:48.031
♪♪

38:48.033 --> 38:49.032
MOM?

38:52.900 --> 38:56.198
HEY, HONEY.
HEY, BE CAREFUL.

38:56.200 --> 38:57.865
THE NURSE SAID NOT TO MOVE
TOO MUCH, OKAY?

38:57.867 --> 39:02.932
OKAY.
YOU SLEPT HERE ALL NIGHT?

39:02.934 --> 39:04.798
OF COURSE I DID.

39:04.800 --> 39:07.532
I DIDN'T WANT YOU TO WAKE UP
ALONE IN SOME STRANGE PLACE.

39:11.334 --> 39:13.665
AM I OKAY?

39:13.667 --> 39:16.998
ULTIMATELY, MM-HMM.

39:17.000 --> 39:19.798
YOU'RE GONNA HEAL
FROM THIS SURGERY.

39:19.800 --> 39:22.432
YOU'RE GONNA BE BACK TO YOUR
NORMAL SELF VERY SOON.

39:25.134 --> 39:27.332
THEN WHY DO YOU LOOK
SO WORRIED?

39:31.467 --> 39:33.765
THERE WAS A
COMPLICATION, SWEETHEART.

39:37.000 --> 39:39.232
THEY HAD TO REMOVE
YOUR OVARIES.

39:42.600 --> 39:49.598
WHAT DOES THAT MEAN?
I CAN'T HAVE CHILDREN EVER?

39:49.600 --> 39:53.799
IF YOU WANT TO BE A MAMA,
YOU'RE GONNA BE A MAMA.

39:53.801 --> 39:56.865
YOU'LL HAVE LOTS OF OPTIONS.
YOU CAN ADOPT.

39:56.867 --> 40:02.532
OH, I KNOW.
I KNOW.

40:03.267 --> 40:07.332
I KNOW IT DOESN'T SEEM LIKE IT,
BUT IT'S GONNA BE OKAY.

40:07.334 --> 40:09.598
[ CRYING ]

40:09.600 --> 40:13.132
BABY, GOD HAS GOT YOU.
GOD HAS GOT YOU.

40:13.134 --> 40:16.265
YOU CAN LEAN ON HIM.

40:16.267 --> 40:20.732
WHY WOULD HE LET
THIS HAPPEN? WHY?

40:20.734 --> 40:24.465
[ SOBBING ]

40:24.467 --> 40:26.632
I WISH
I HAD THE ANSWER.

40:29.400 --> 40:31.965
I WISH I DID.

40:35.901 --> 40:37.999
-MAY I?
-OF COURSE.

40:40.667 --> 40:44.265
HOW CAN I BE
OF ASSISTANCE?

40:44.267 --> 40:47.931
UM, IT'S NOT WHAT I WANT,
BUT I HEAR YOU,

40:47.933 --> 40:52.732
AND HAVING HEARD YOU
AND HAVING PRAYED ON IT MYSELF,

40:52.734 --> 40:59.432
WELL, I TOO NOW SEE
NO CHOICE.

41:03.334 --> 41:04.865
WHAT'S THIS?

41:04.867 --> 41:07.398
IT'S A DRAFT OF WHAT I THINK WE
SHOULD TELL THE CHURCH SUNDAY.

41:07.400 --> 41:11.598
FEEL FREE TO MAKE
ANY CHANGES YOU SEE FIT.

41:11.600 --> 41:13.732
I TRUST
YOUR JUDGMENT.

41:16.900 --> 41:18.199
AND, MAE...

41:23.667 --> 41:24.832
I'M SORRY.

41:28.400 --> 41:31.431
PLEASE CLOSE THE DOOR
BEHIND YOU.

